      "raw_text": "10y United Press Leased Wlre)\n\n\nTACOMA, May 12.-I. B. Rich\nards, who has been general super\nintendent of transportation of the\nNorthern Pacific at st. Paul, today\nbecame general superintendent of\nthe lines west of Paradise, Mont,\nwith headquarters in Tacoma, sue\nceeding B. e. Palmer, who has re-\nsigned. Announcement of this\nchange came as surprise to rail-\nroad men, owing to the prominence\nof the officials concerned, both of\nwhom are well known throughout\nthe northwest.\n\n\nRichards will arrive in Tacoma\nMonday to assume the RESPONSE\nbility of operating the Northern\nPacific lines from the Tacoma\nheadquarters.\n\n\n+ Richards began his railroad ca\nreer in this city as telegrapher\n20 years ago."
